verbose_text: However, one study by Hakkinen and Pakarinen [XREF_BIBR] showed no statistical change in cortisol levels among women in three different age groups (30 years, 50 years, and 70 years) who performed the same heavy resistance exercise protocol while a significant increase in cortisol was observed in the middle aged men compared to the younger and older men, who performed the same heavy resistance exercise protocol and were classified with respect to age, in the same manner as the women who participated in this study [XREF_BIBR].
